containerRayCast uses a SceneContainer->castRay() call, which ignores the physics world - this can be somewhat corrected through the addition of a PHYSICSMGR check and a mPhysicsWorld->castRay() call, but is not suitable as a direct replacement because the function doesn't recognise TypeMasks.

My fix:
Line 1627-ish in sceneContainer.cpp, under `S32 ret = 0;`

```
   if (PHYSICSMGR)
    {
        PhysicsWorld* mPhysicsWorld = PHYSICSMGR->getWorld("server");
        if(mPhysicsWorld->castRay(start, end, &rinfo, Point3F(0, 0, 0)) == true)
           ret = rinfo.object->getId();
    }
```

and of course at the top,

```
    #include "T3D/physics/physicsPlugin.h"
    #include "T3D/physics/physicsWorld.h"
```

and in px3World/whatever the bullet equivalent is you might want to exclude "PX3_PLAYER" as well as the trigger flag already present.

Sources for the "fix":
http://www.garagegames.com/community/forums/viewthread/105537/1#comment-728083
http://www.garagegames.com/community/forums/viewthread/130197

